This covers how to install Python and its package manager, pip. You’ll also need virtualenv to create isolated environments for your projects.

Installing Python and pip:

For Ubuntu:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip

For macOS (using Homebrew):

brew install python3

Setting up a Virtual Environment:

Install virtualenv:

pip3 install virtualenv

Create a virtual environment:

virtualenv elo_env

Activate the virtual environment:

On Linux/macOS:

source elo_env/bin/activate

On Windows:

elo_env\Scripts\activate

Installing Docker:

Docker allows you to containerize the application for easy deployment.

For Ubuntu:

sudo apt install docker.io
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker

For macOS, download Docker Desktop from Docker’s website and follow the installation instructions.

Installing Git:

Version control is crucial for collaborative development.

For Ubuntu:

sudo apt install git

For macOS:

brew install git





